Number = {{14}},
Month = {{JUL 18}},
Abstract = {{Pre- and post-fire vegetational dynamical behaviours in a forest site of
   Northern Italy were investigated, using the 1998 to 2003 time series of
   Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) from SPOT-VEGETATION
   sensor. The detrended fluctuation analysis (DFA) was adopted to detect
   persistent behaviour, in order to characterize the stability/instability
   properties of vegetation dynamics. Our analysis points to the following
   results: i) both pre- and post-fire vegetation dynamics are persistent;
   ii) post-fire dynamical behaviour is characterized by a larger degree of
   persistence; iii) a link between persistence and resilience can be
   identified.}},
